                            <comment id="141440" author="adilger" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2016 21:27:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The recent failures of test_7c are related to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7737&quot; title=&quot;osd_handler.c:2777:osd_object_destroy()) ASSERTION( !lu_object_is_dying(dt-&amp;gt;do_lu.lo_header) &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-7737&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-7737&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, with the ASSERTION message on the MDS1 console log.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="141402" author="jay" created="Fri, 5 Feb 2016 18:26:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;new occurrence at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/0660da7c-cc02-11e5-901d-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/0660da7c-cc02-11e5-901d-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have seen this happened in my recent patch twice, but I didn&apos;t see any occurrence in the previous version of my patch. I wonder if there is a recent landing worsening the problem&lt;/p&gt;
